      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="key-takeaway-structure-social-content-for-ai-extra"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Quality beats quantity for search optimization. One keyword-optimized post per day on your primary platform outperforms five feed-focused posts. For multi-platform strategies: YouTube — 1-2 videos per week, TikTok — 1 per day, Instagram — 4-7 per week, LinkedIn — 3-5 per week, Pinterest — 2-5 fresh pins daily, Reddit — 3-5 valuable comments plus 1 original post per week.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="key-takeaway-consistency-matters-more-than-frequen">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Key takeaway: Consistency matters more than frequency. A sustainable schedule you can maintain for 6 months beats an aggressive schedule you abandon in 2 weeks. What is the Social Visibility Stack?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="key-takeaway-consistency-matters-more-than-frequen"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>The Social Visibility Stack is a 5-layer framework for building cross-platform search authority. Layer 1 is Foundation — keyword-optimized profiles on every platform. Layer 2 is Content — keyword-aligned publishing. Layer 3 is Engagement — generating authority signals through comments, shares, and saves. Layer 4 is Cross-Platform — creating an authority loop where each platform reinforces the others. Layer 5 is AI Citation — structuring content so AI systems cite it as authoritative.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="key-takeaway-build-the-stack-in-order-each-layer-m">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Key takeaway: Build the stack in order. Each layer makes the next one more effective. Can I automate social SEO?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="key-takeaway-build-the-stack-in-order-each-layer-m"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes, portions of social SEO can be automated. Keyword research, content scheduling, analytics reporting, and cross-posting are all automatable. However, engagement — responding to comments, participating in communities, building relationships — requires human interaction. The most effective approach combines automation for repetitive tasks with personal engagement for relationship building.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="key-takeaway-automate-creation-and-distribution-ke">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Key takeaway: Automate creation and distribution. Keep engagement human. How do I measure social SEO ROI?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="key-takeaway-automate-creation-and-distribution-ke"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Track these metrics monthly: profile visits from search (platform analytics), non-follower impressions (discovery metric), social referral traffic (Google Analytics 4), branded search volume (Google Search Console), video search rankings (YouTube Studio), and AI citation mentions (manual checks). Set month-over-month growth targets and adjust your strategy based on which platforms and content types drive the most measurable results.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="key-takeaway-measure-search-driven-metrics-not-van">
      <span class="faq-q-text">Key takeaway: Measure search-driven metrics, not vanity metrics like follower count. What should I stop doing for social SEO in 2026?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="key-takeaway-measure-search-driven-metrics-not-van"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Stop hashtag stuffing — use 3-5 relevant hashtags maximum. Stop posting without keyword intent — every post should target a search query. Stop ignoring alt text and file names — they are indexed by platforms and Google. Stop treating platforms in isolation — build a unified cross-platform strategy. Stop chasing viral content — search-optimized content generates sustained traffic while viral content spikes and dies.</p></div></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p><strong>Key takeaway:</strong> The tactics that worked in 2022 actively hurt visibility in 2026.</p>
<p>Social SEO in 2026 rewards the businesses that execute consistently. The tactics above are not secrets. They are fundamentals that most businesses ignore because they require discipline, not creativity.</p>
<p>The brands that win will not be the ones with the best content. They will be the ones that show up every day, optimized for search, across every platform where their audience looks for answers.</p>
<p>Start with your profiles. Add keyword intent to every post. Build the Social Visibility Stack one layer at a time. And measure what matters.</p>
<p>Your audience is searching right now. The only question is whether they will find you.</p>
